# Text Elements
Bottom up parsing: beginning at the leaves (the bottom) and working up towards the root (the top) ^vgk1dsgg

Note: 
since the reverse of rightmost derivation would be
to reduce the leftmost symbols to the right
we can scan the input from the left to right.

Once we encounter a handle(on the top of the stack) we would reduce ^CAgDcfpn

derivation:  ^kPnK4RaV

our goal is to identify what the 
'body' of the prev production applied (handle)
and undo the changes ^L8FexUSU

'new symbols', 
ie: the body of the prev production applied ^qOGdJ5Ip

right sequential forms
are the string of terminal/non-terminals that are found after applying 1/more productions.
meaning the start symbol itself is also one

Note: a right sequential form with no non-terminals are also called a 'sentence' ^f11k45Z1

everything after the handle is are terminal.

because its a rightmost derivation(non-terminals are alrdy expanded into terminals) ^lKmHEYr1

this is not a handle despite having a production of the form F->id
because reducing it into F DOES NOT produce a right sequential form 
of a RIGHTMOST derivation

F*F cannot be derived from any rightmost derivation in the given grammar

Hence: the F circles is actly the rightmost handle! ^D4AXyN97

because when u think about it, we always apply the productions into the rightmost non-terminal
which guarantees:

1) everything to the right of the non-terminal/the new symbols inserted only consists of terminals
2) the 'handle' we should reduce should be the rightmost handle we identify 
       Note: we must reduce the longest handle length too for the rightmost handle
             if input = F*id, and possible productions are T->F and T->F*id
             we want to read(shift) until we have F*id and then we only find out that there arent more handles possible(which makes it the rightmost)
             and we reduce using T->F*id ^KAAMZ6Ti

Hence: the productions to use for each right sequential form 
can be only the one used in its derivation. Which gives 1 and only 1 handle for each right sequential form
 ^2ahiMFd0

Handle Pruning ^J3YwOfvX
